00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:22.000
energy difference.
And so, if then I apply a potential,

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:26.000
let's say I make this side of the
crystal negative,

00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:30.000
and I make the side of the crystal
positive, it takes a tiny bit of

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:34.000
energy to pull an electron out of
the topmost orbital,

00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:38.000
put it up here, and now it's free to
move about the crystal.

00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:42.000
So, this accounts for the high
