00:15:39.350 --> 00:15:43.210
So, that gives us a sense of what's
going on in the conductivity of

00:15:43.210 --> 00:15:47.070
something like copper or sodium.
But, now let's think about

00:15:47.070 --> 00:15:51.310
something like magnesium.
Magnesium is a metal.

00:15:51.310 --> 00:15:55.930
But let's think about what's going
on with magnesium.

00:15:55.930 --> 00:16:00.560
Magnesium has 3s, but it has 3s2 in
the case of magnesium.

00:16:00.560 --> 00:16:05.180
Magnesium is 3s2. So,
if we start filling magnesium s-band,

00:16:05.180 --> 00:16:09.800
we're going to fill two by two all
